\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.10}{\ignorespaces Statistical anatomy of the $56$-feature fusion space. (a) Linear discriminant: the trust signal is linearly separable ($98.2\%$ train accuracy). (b) Unsupervised PCA: the classes overlap, so the dominant variance is scene difference, not the class signal. (c) Per-feature single-feature AUROC. (d) Leakage map (Eq.~\ref {eq:leakage}): the lower-right region is robust signal (high AUROC, near-zero leakage); the upper-left is scene fingerprint (chance-level AUROC, leakage in the hundreds). Source: \textsc  {Ledger}~fusion-feature-leakage; \texttt  {classifier/fusion\_feature\_stats.py}.}}{61}{figure.caption.38}\protected@file@percent }
